## Creating a new resource
- Click&nbsp;**Create**&nbsp;in the **Resources** table.![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Select the **Type** of resource that you wish to create from the list.

- In the&nbsp;**Alias** field, enter the name of the new resource.

- Configure any additional parameters, depending on the resource type.

> Note

For more information, see: [Doxee Platform Repository Resource Reference](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-repository-resource-reference).

## Managing resources
Select one or more resource to view the available actions.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Note

The available actions depend on the resource type.

Actions that are available on individual resources may not be available on a multiple selection (for example, the **Rename** action).

Icon

Action

Description

![](data:image/png;base64,)

[**Edit**](#)

Edit the resource.

> Note

This action is only available for editable resources (for example, Batch workflow).

![](data:image/png;base64,)

[**Release**](#)

Open the&nbsp;Release &amp; Deploy panel for the resource, which provides more information on the released versions and active deployments of the resource.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Rename**

Edit the name of the resource.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

[**Copy**](#)

Create a copy of the resource.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

[**Move**](#)

Move the resource to a different folder.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

[**Transfer**](#DoxeePlatformRepositoryManagingResources-transfer)

Transfer the resource to a different account.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

[**Download**](#)

Download the resource file.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

[**Remove**](#)

Delete the resource.

> Tip

You may also hover on the name of a resource, click on the **...** icon that appears, and select one of the available actions from the context menu. For example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

### Copying or moving a resource
- Select a resource.

- Click&nbsp;![](data:image/png;base64,)&nbsp;(**Copy**)&nbsp;or&nbsp;![](data:image/png;base64,)&nbsp;(**Move**).

- Select the destination folder. For example:&nbsp;![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Click&nbsp;**Copy**&nbsp;or&nbsp;**Move&nbsp;**to confirm.

> Tip

By default, the system suggests copying the resource to the current folder, or moving it to a subfolder of the current folder.

You may use the breadcrumb links at the top to browse different Repository folders, or search for a specific folder name using the **Search** function.

### Transferring a resource
- Select a resource.

- Click&nbsp;![](data:image/png;base64,)&nbsp;(**Transfer**). The&nbsp;**Transfer Resources** dialog appears; for example:![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Select the destination account from the drop-down menu on the top-left.

- Select the destination folder.

- Click **Transfer&nbsp;**to confirm.

> Tip

You may search for a specific folder name within the selected account using the **Search** function.

### Removing a resource
- Select a resource.

- Click&nbsp;![](data:image/png;base64,)&nbsp;(**Remove**). A confirmation message is displayed.![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Click&nbsp;**Remove** to confirm.

> Warning

The **Remove** operation is irreversible.

If the resource has been deployed, if you delete it from the Repository the actual deployment will not be removed from the tenant. 

### Downloading a resource
- Select a resource.

- Click&nbsp;![](data:image/png;base64,)&nbsp;(**Download**) to save a copy of the resource file to your local filesystem.

### Editing a resource
- Select a resource.

- Click&nbsp;![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Edit**) to open it in the corresponding editor.

> Note

This action is only available for editable resources (for example, Batch workflow).

### Viewing the releases &amp; deployments of a resource&nbsp;
The **Release &amp; Deploy** panel provides more information on the released versions and active deployments of the selected resource.

- Select a resource.

- Click&nbsp;![](data:image/png;base64,)&nbsp;(**Release**).

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Note

For more information, see: [Doxee Platform Repository - Release &amp; Deploy Panel](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-repository-release-amp-deploy-panel).
